  "prompt": "I have had immense problems with my HP Envy laptop. I really want to get it replaced or get my money back. What should I do?",
  "response": "Here are some steps you can take:\n\n1. Check warranty status\n- If still under warranty, contact HP Support directly\n- They may repair, replace, or refund your laptop\n\n2. Gather documentation\n- Original purchase receipt\n- Warranty information\n- Detailed list of problems you've experienced\n\n3. Contact HP Customer Support\n- Call their support line\n- Open a support ticket online\n- Explain your issues thoroughly\n- Request replacement or refund\n\n4. If unsatisfied with HP's response\n- File a complaint with Better Business Bureau\n- Contact the retailer where you purchased the laptop\n- Consider legal options as a last resort\n\n5. If purchased recently\n- Check return policy of original retailer\n- You might be able to return within a specific timeframe\n\n6. Document everything\n- Keep records of all communications\n- Take screenshots of issues\n- Note dates and times of problems\n\nTips:\n- Be calm and professional\n- Clearly explain the recurring problems\n- Request specific resolution\n- Escalate to supervisor if needed\n\nWould you like help drafting a complaint or finding HP support contact information?",
